---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Control Responsibility Matrix | BeaconGuard Assurance"
  description="BeaconGuard responsibility boundaries for Deterministic Playbook Evaluation, application enforcement, governed systems, systems of record, and reviewers."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Control Responsibility Matrix</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This page helps reviewers understand which responsibilities BeaconGuard owns, which remain with the application and system of record, and which stay outside BeaconGuard's control boundary. It is intended to reduce ambiguity during architecture, security, risk, and procurement review.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Responsibility model</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard governs whether a request may proceed to governed execution under an Active Verified Release, returning ALLOW or DENY only.
      BeaconGuard does not replace transaction systems, systems of record, model or API providers,
      or downstream operational ownership. Human review via a Verifiable Decision Record obligation does not permit execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Responsibility Matrix</h2>
    <div class="responsibility-matrix-wrap">
      <table class="responsibility-matrix">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Responsibility</th>
            <th>BeaconGuard</th>
            <th>Application</th>
            <th>Governed system provider</th>
            <th>System of record</th>
            <th>Operations / reviewers</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Authorization decision at the Runtime Control Boundary</td>
            <td>Owns Deterministic Playbook Evaluation and explicit ALLOW or DENY decisioning</td>
            <td>Submits trusted request context (or via System Connector) and enforces returned decision</td>
            <td>Does not own authorization policy</td>
            <td>Does not own request authorization</td>
            <td>Review boundary correctness and Compliance Playbook fit</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Business transaction execution</td>
            <td>Does not execute business transactions</td>
            <td>Orchestrates allowed workflow steps after ALLOW</td>
            <td>Does not execute business transactions on BeaconGuard's behalf</td>
            <td>Remains authoritative for transaction/state recording</td>
            <td>Validate control separation and escalation paths</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Model / API / automation behavior and output quality</td>
            <td>Does not claim quality or business correctness of governed systems</td>
            <td>Determines how allowed outputs are used</td>
            <td>Owns serving characteristics of the governed system</td>
            <td>Does not determine model or API quality</td>
            <td>Evaluate suitability and downstream control expectations</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Decision evidence and review context</td>
            <td>Emits Verifiable Decision Records with release identity and decision context</td>
            <td>Correlates BeaconGuard decisions with workflow context as needed</td>
            <td>Does not provide BeaconGuard decision evidence</td>
            <td>May hold downstream business records, not BeaconGuard decision evidence by default</td>
            <td>Review evidence, reconstruct decisions, and assess control operation</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Fail-closed behavior when required conditions are not met</td>
            <td>Returns DENY when release, trust, approval, freshness, or replay conditions are missing, malformed, or out of bounds</td>
            <td>Must respect and enforce DENY outcomes; must not treat review as permission</td>
            <td>Does not control BeaconGuard fail-closed semantics</td>
            <td>Not responsible for request gating</td>
            <td>Validate that failure handling is explicit and reviewable</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Active Verified Release and evidence provider operations</td>
            <td>Defines release verification expectations and evidence record shape</td>
            <td>Consumes only activated releases in the governed path</td>
            <td>Out of scope</td>
            <td>Out of scope</td>
            <td>Customer configures evidence provider durability and monitors release activation</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>What reviewers should verify</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The application submits the trusted request context BeaconGuard requires (signed metadata, workflow identity, role, trust, pathway, freshness, and related inputs)</li>
      <li>BeaconGuard's ALLOW or DENY response is enforced before governed execution</li>
      <li>Absent approval yields DENY (for example APPROVAL_REQUIRED), not a permission-to-execute review state</li>
      <li>Governed system behavior is not treated as the authorization boundary</li>
      <li>Systems of record remain authoritative for business state</li>
      <li>Reviewers can distinguish Verifiable Decision Records from downstream business records</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Next step</h2>
    <p>Reviewers can continue structured evaluation through the Reviewer Kit, Trust Center, and Contact path.</p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/reviewer-kit">Open Reviewer Kit</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/trust-assurance">Review Trust Center</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/contact">Continue via contact</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
